U.S. solar stocks are enjoying their best day in almost a month, with the rooftop installer Vivint Solar Inc. climbing the most in nine months. Exactly what’s behind Tuesday’s rally is debatable. Here’s what a few analysts are saying: Vivint rose as much as 16 percent to $3.90, the biggest intraday gain since June 20. SunPower Corp., the second-biggest U.S. panel maker, rose as much as 8.2 percent, the most intraday since January.